const faqs = [
  {
    question: "When does the missed call text send?",
    answer: "The text dispatches within seconds of the unanswered call ending — before the main contractor calls the next cladding firm on his subcontract list. During full-day commercial installations where every team member is at height from first light to last panel, this automatic text maintains your firm's commercial presence without a single person descending the MEWP."
  },
  {
    question: "What does the text message say?",
    answer: "The message wording is entirely yours — created during setup and adjustable at any time. An effective cladding message reads: 'Thank you for calling [company name]. We are currently installing cladding on a commercial project. We will return your call at the earliest opportunity. Reply with your cladding requirements for a faster response.' This signals active capability and invites specification sharing."
  },
  {
    question: "Does this replace AI Phone Answering?",
    answer: "They complement each other as layered protection for your cladding business. Phone Answering holds complete conversations — identifying the panel system, area, building height, fire classification, and programme. Missed Call Text Back handles uncommon edge cases — a call during a critical alignment when the panel is half-fixed, a mobile signal blocked by the building facade, or a caller hanging up before the system connects. Running both guarantees zero missed cladding opportunities."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does Missed Call Text Back cost?",
