  scenario="It is 3:30pm on a windy Thursday in March. Strong gusts have halted MEWP work above the third floor on your current commercial site in Didcot — company policy stops platform work above 35mph. Your crew is instead installing ground-floor cavity barriers on the east elevation. Seven missed calls between 8am and 3:30pm. Without Missed Call Text Back, you check at 4pm: seven unknowns, one voicemail — 'timber cladding for an extension' — six permanently lost. With Missed Call Text Back, all seven received texts. Reply one: 'architect Oxford — specifying Equitone fibre cement for a GP surgery extension, about 350 sqm, need a cladding contractor with Equitone experience.' Reply two: 'homeowner Summertown — wants cedar shiplap on a garden room, about 28 sqm.' Reply three: 'QS Bicester — variation to existing school cladding contract, need to discuss additional canopy cladding.' Reply four: 'main contractor Banbury — new warehouse, profiled steel, 2,400 sqm, need tender.' Reply five: 'facilities manager Headington — wind damage, two composite panels dislodged on a four-storey office, need emergency assessment.' Reply six: 'self-builder Charlbury — zinc and timber mixed facade, 200 sqm total, contemporary barn conversion.' Reply seven: 'architect Abingdon — remediation enquiry, ACM panels on a 2006 apartment block.' Seven leads. Friday you prioritise — the emergency panel assessment first, the 2,400 sqm warehouse tender second, the GP surgery third."
